description:
&lt;p&gt;Portsmouth University Hospitals NHS Trust is the largest non-teaching hospital trust in England. With strong local ties and serving around 675,000 residents in Portsmouth and South East Hampshire, they pride themselves on providing comprehensive acute and specialist services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking experienced and motivated &lt;strong&gt;Call Handlers&lt;/strong&gt; with Call Centre experience to join the Portsmouth Staff Bank at Queen Alexandra Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The shifts available are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;6am to 12:45pm (incl 30 mins unpaid break) and 12:45pm – 19:30pm (incl. 30 mins unpaid break). You will be required to work 5 out of 7 days. Please only apply if you are available to work these hours. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Corporate HR Manager in the day to day operational delivery of Staff Support Line services ensuring a comprehensive, high quality staff absence calls and emails handling service is provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for the day to day answering of staff calls ensuring continued personal and professional development and work completion, as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide assistance and support to new and existing staff in terms of timely call handling, answering queries and following the relevant, up to date guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the training and buddying with the new SSL Team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use own initiative in the planning and prioritising of own workload to ensure that deadlines are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seek advice and guidance from line manager if needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain good channels of communication to ensure line manager is kept aware of issues and concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills &amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum 5 GCSE’s (or equivalent)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good Telephone Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work independently or as part of a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self motivated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible approach to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound IT Skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Telephone Manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to use own initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow and interpret policies and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure and remain calm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bank workers are invaluable to us and in return of your hard work and commitment we can offer the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay rates – enhanced payrates paid during the weekend and Bank Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working pattern&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to work across sites, gaining invaluable knowledge and experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority placements over an Agency Workers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated onsite bookings team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronic timesheet submission and weekly pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An onsite office and designated Business Partners to offer daily support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A professional compliance team that will ensure you remain compliant to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We also offer Core Skills Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply directly to this advertisement, ensuring you upload a full and up to date CV. Successful applicants will be contacted shortly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you require further information then please contact the Portsmouth Staff Bank Recruitment Team on 0333 577 3316.&lt;/p&gt;
